        descLong: "Self type (Python 3.11+, via typing_extensions) represents the class of the current instance. Use it in methods that return self (fluent/builder APIs) or create copies (clone, copy). Without Self, you'd need to hardcode return types or use generics awkwardly. Essential for method chaining and factory patterns.",
